20 September 2019 - Tharina Human, Laetitia Nel and Pieter Jacobus van Zyl in the dock on day two of their bail application in the Amy'Leigh de Jager kidnapping case. JOHANNESBURG - Three suspects accused of kidnapping Amy'Leigh de Jager, will continue with their bail application at the Vanderbijlpark Magistrate's Court on Tuesday. READ: Fourth suspect in Amy'Leigh kidnapping to appear in court The six-year-old was snatched outside her school, early in September after her mother dropped her off. Police arrested Laetitia Nel, Pieter van Zyl and Tharina Human, who is a teacher at the school. Human is said to have been the mastermind of the abduction. READ: Amy'Leigh kidnapped to 'save suspect's daughter' Fourth suspect, Bofokeng Molemohi, made his first appearance last week. He will return to court on Wednesday.